abstract: When I gave up law and started being a clown, I knew what it meant to be happy.
snippet: When I gave up law and started being a clown, I knew what it meant to be happy.
lead_paragraph: I was the envy of my 30-something friends in Palo Alto, Calif. I had my own law office right on California Avenue. People charged with crimes handed me cash, in advance, over a big oak desk. Occasionally, I’d make a couple of grand in an afternoon.

abstract: Maxima’s attitude is a reminder of Generation 3, the one first marketed as a four-door sports car. The new model is now a bit longer and lower.
snippet: Maxima’s attitude is a reminder of Generation 3, the one first marketed as a four-door sports car. The new model is now a bit longer and lower.
lead_paragraph: NISSAN has offered few reasons for buyers to step up from a loaded Altima to the Maxima the last few years. Many of the same features and much of the same performance and design panache in the Maxima could be had with its less expensive sibling. There was no 2015 Maxima, and what 2014 models remained were sold to loyalists (and there are many) — until the 2016 models arrived this summer.
headline_main: Video Review: New Maxima Gives Nissan Fans a Reason to Trade Up
headline_print_headline: New Maxima Gives Nissan Fans a Reason to Trade Up

abstract: Mr. Johnston was behind “Blonde on Blonde,” “At Folsom Prison” and some classic albums by Simon and Garfunkel.
snippet: Mr. Johnston was behind “Blonde on Blonde,” “At Folsom Prison” and some classic albums by Simon and Garfunkel.
lead_paragraph: Bob Johnston, who produced a string of classic albums in the 1960s and ’70s including Bob Dylan’s “Highway 61 Revisited” and “Blonde on Blonde” and Johnny Cash’s “At Folsom Prison,” died on Friday in Gallatin, Tenn. He was 83.

abstract: The plunging value of government bonds has hurt tens of thousands of Puerto Ricans, and a restructuring of the debt could heap more hardship on them.

lead_paragraph: To Lev Steinberg, it seemed like a good place to park his nest egg.

abstract: In a country where corruption saturates government at virtually all levels, conspiracy theories are running rampant on how Joaquín Guzmán Loera fled prison.
snippet: In a country where corruption saturates government at virtually all levels, conspiracy theories are running rampant on how Joaquín Guzmán Loera fled prison.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — When Mexico’s most powerful drug lord, Joaquín Guzmán Loera, escaped from prison last month, he walked out of captivity and straight into the conspiracy-obsessed imaginations of his countrymen, who are willing, it seems, to believe almost anything except what their government tells them.

lead_paragraph: The Porsche 911 was an instant classic when first seen at the Frankfurt auto show in 1963. The 911 has always been shorthand for top-notch performance, engineering and peer envy, and after 50 years, the teardrop silhouette remains as constant as Ray-Ban aviators.

abstract: Having to answer questions about President Obama’s aggressive actions on climate, those vying for president might have to debate what they will do to his climate legacy.
snippet: Having to answer questions about President Obama’s aggressive actions on climate, those vying for president might have to debate what they will do to his climate legacy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The issue of climate change played almost no role in the 2012 presidential campaign. President Obama barely mentioned the topic, nor did the Republican nominee, Mitt Romney. It was not raised in a single presidential debate.
